                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="197253" author="adilger" created="Sun, 28 May 2017 06:41:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is no longer an issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="18618" author="mjmac" created="Mon, 1 Aug 2011 22:19:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is due to the requested EL6 kernel update.  Due to the way EL6&apos;s anaconda works now, it is not possible to specify that an older kernel should be installed when a newer one is available in the repos.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="18615" author="sarah" created="Mon, 1 Aug 2011 19:19:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;got this issue again on the latest tag 2.0.66 build #228&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;root@client-15 tests&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;# uname -a&lt;br/&gt;
Linux client-15.lab.whamcloud.com 2.6.32-131.6.1.el6.x86_64 #1 SMP Mon Jun 20 14:15:38 EDT 2011 x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;root@client-15 tests&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;# rpm -qa|grep lustre&lt;br/&gt;
lustre-client-tests-2.0.66-2.6.32_131.2.1.el6.x86_64.x86_64&lt;br/&gt;
lustre-client-modules-2.0.66-2.6.32_131.2.1.el6.x86_64.x86_64&lt;br/&gt;
lustre-client-2.0.66-2.6.32_131.2.1.el6.x86_64.x86_64&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16301" author="mjmac" created="Tue, 14 Jun 2011 10:59:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This ticket and TT-136 are basically for the same issue.  As that ticket has been resolved, this one should be as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14768" author="mjmac" created="Fri, 20 May 2011 09:52:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve taken the kludgy approach for now and removed the 2.6.32-71.29.1.el6 kernel RPMs from the local mirror.  I&apos;ll try to find a better solution soon, as this problem hinders our ability to test multiple kernel versions.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14757" author="mjmac" created="Fri, 20 May 2011 09:35:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This appears to be a problem with the EL6 installer.  In short, even though the kickstart is specifying the correct kernel, EL6 is choosing the newest kernel it sees.  This wasn&apos;t a problem until I added the latest errata kernel to the local yum mirror for EL6 (for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-343&quot; title=&quot;kernel update [rhel6 2.6.32-71.29.1]&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-343&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-343&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As a short-term kludge, I can remove the 2.6.32-71.29.1.el6 kernel.  Longer-term, this is a bug in EL6 (or a change in behavior that I consider a bug).  I&apos;ll poke around in RH&apos;s bugzilla to see if this is a known issue which may have been addressed in EL6.1.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14656" author="pjones" created="Thu, 19 May 2011 06:25:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Brian&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can you please look at this one?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
